sing the power of markets to create opportunity for people to improve their lives around the world they invest in and help scale innovative organizations to catalyze economic social and political change focusing on the themes of access to capital and media markets and transparency this talk is intended to broaden student understanding of the attorney's role in international philantrophy and in particular the way that attorneys working at internationally focused philantrophic organizations have to navigate international and domestic law to achieve positive social change please rsvp to the link below http www stanford edu dept law forms fitzgerald fb lunch will be provided location room 280b topics investment organizations search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages events of interest us and bulgaria new eu member new opportunities his excellency john r beyrle her excellency elena poptodorova smart green cities new technologies new strategies new practices shorenstein aparc special event pdf+ china's fifth generation takes the helm new leaders new challenges and structural constraints thomas fingar new beginnings toward a new era of us south korean partnership michael h armacost robert carlin don oberdorfer charles l jack pritchard evans jr revere gi wook shin pdf+ support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
